<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>egarding this other situation....Karadin you talk about how you are the 'effected' guild and you want blood etc... let's play a little game.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It's about precedent, already we have FK pointing to some VOLS/ED Trak issue I know nothing about as a reason they should be allowed to get away with KSing our King Tormax.  Where does it end?  If you guys get away with it, then people have two precedents, next thing you know, rotations mean nothing, and people can kill out of turn and just say &quot;oops, sorry about that&quot;, and everything is ok.  That's a wrong answer in my book.<br>
<br>
If ED/VOLS were able to work out their differences without involving the RTA, that is between them, and has nothing to do with FK/NB.  Personally, I think whoever KSed Trak should be punished, but it doesn't involve me.  However, the KT situation does, and this wasn't just a mistake, it was completely mishandled from A to Z.  You killed a mob that wasn't up for 24 hours, you didn't send a tell or ask in RTA before you killed him under &quot;FFA&quot; rules, you didn't send a tell or ask in RTA AFTER you killed him when you realized you messed up.  You left NB to find out on  its own that KT had been KSed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Let's say it was two...three hours later, or whatever long enough to have a confirmed uptime on Tormax of 24 hours and FK HAD killed him 'legally' under the Christmas rules.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Sure, I'll play that game, that means FK would have waited until 4pm PST on Saturday to kill him.  I am ok with that, because if we ever took 16 hours to kill King Tormax, I would probably /guilddisband.  Let's review the timeline here:<br>
<br>
8 pm PST (11 EST) Thursday servers crash<br>
12 am PST Friday Karadin checks on KT to see in what order NB should plan their mobs (yay for SoS)<br>
4 pm PST Friday Karadin recieves a tell from Malystrx of VoF that King Tormax is up<br>
9pm PST (12 pm EST) Friday King Tormax is killed by FK<br>
12am PST Friday NB moves to Kael to kill KT, but he is already dead.<br>
<br>
Explain to me first how it happened.  Wait, that's been done, with two different stories.  First story, KT was up over 24 hours (all but impossible given that server crash was 25 hours before you killed him, he would have had to spawn on server up: he hadn't even spawn 4 hours after server up, I checked).  Second story, that an entire guild of mostly above college age people misread Vince's post about special holiday rotation exceptions and thought every mob was FFA.  This was able to happen because both RTA reps for FK were conveniently missing at the time (Jlxaac and Jurassic), and couldn't correct the misunderstanding about the post.<br>
<br>
Now explain something even more basic.  I got ZERO tells from anyone even remotely affiliated with FK leadership before they went to kill KT (I was on all day).  I saw ZERO questions in RTA channel about &quot;Hey, KT has been up over 24 hours, we're gonna kill him under FFA, ok?&quot;.  I got ZERO tells AFTER you killed him and Jlxaac knew you guys had killed out of turn.  Why?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>FK is guilty of bad manners towards NB in this case, but I somehow think it would be hard for you to dislike us more anyway.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The only thing I dislike about FK is the dual-wielded chips you seem to wear firmly planted on both shoulders.  I have had Jlxaac, Fere, Eros, Xarien, Dannis, and many other FK members on NB raids in the last 3 years (gladly and with much respect).  I'm the one who opened Jaled Dar's door for Sylph to do his ST key turn in.  Yah, you caught me Jurassic, I just love to hate FK, it's my driving force in life (/sarcasm off).  Hell, I remember when most of you weren't FK, but wore Far Runner tags and we were all in one big happy alliance together back in the day for planar raids.  I have no reason to dislike you save the one I just listed, namely that you guys seem to have such a big problem with us to include even the most basic of communications on rotation mobs.<br>
<br>
The reason NB doesn't find itself in this situation is because Milambus and I make damn sure to be certain we are communicate with the rest of the community on any questionable mobs we are going to kill.  If something has been up 24 hours, I check with the guild in question first before moving on it.  Why?  Because its that important to maintain the basic premise of rotations - that you don't kill out of order.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Now if you be the bigger man, let the precedent stand in this situation then NB STILL takes the next Tormax, and FK skips their upcoming Tormax and NB gets their NEXT tormax one spawn sooner then if we had killed him legit that night anyway.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This isn't about being practical and caring how soon we get our next KT and the one after that.  It's about precedent and complete disregard for the most basic part of a rotation.  All your recommendation does is allow FK to walk away without so much as a slap on the wrist for forcibly switching places in the rotation with us.  You &quot;skipping&quot; the next turn is a joke, as you aren't &quot;skipping&quot; anything, you ALREADY killed this turn, you just did it three weeks earlier than you would have if you followed rotation order.  How does letting you get away with this make me a bigger or better man?  I understand we all make mistakes, but come on.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It's all ready been said how embarrased we are as a collective entity of assing it up so badly, we have and are continuing to take internal measures to make sure nothing like this can ever happen again. FK fully supports the RTA and what it stands for.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
None of your raid leaders are ebayed newbs with no clue about how rotations work.  They've already all been on this server, working with the system for well over two years.  What steps are you taking to &quot;train&quot; these seasoned veterans on how to send /tell GuildLeaderX to work out issues ahead of time?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>However we have no desire to be 'punished' for this stupid mistake then any other guild who also made this same mistake.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
We would voluntarily take this &quot;punishment&quot;, or penalty for making this kind of error.  BotS has already done so twice in the last 4 months on Cursed rotation situations.  We haven't had to yet, because as I cited above, we put a lot of effort into making sure we don't make these kinds of mistakes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sylph@therathetravelagency>Sylph</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Frayed Knot - GL</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/31/02 8:06:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=238.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   blah</span><hr size=1> First off, as already explianed, FK was under the mistaken impression that KT was FFA (yes our college grads can skim a post and miss something), why would we contact anyone?  Would NB send us a tell if they were about to kill Lozidal?  I fail to see your logic here Karadin.<br>
<br>
Currently this is how the KT rot stands<br>
NB - TL - LoM - FK - VoF - LoL - BotS - SotE<br>
<br>
Fk going out of turn directly effects 3 guilds, NB, TL, LoM. I fail to understand why people seem to think this is just an issue with NB, our mistake effected TL and LoM just as much.  Our mistake also indirectly effected the rest of the guilds on the KT rotation.<br>
<br>
As for skippin turns, easy to make that punishment for yourself where there are 2 or 3 guilds on a 3 day rotation.  Skipping one KT spawn equates to 5 months with the current guilds on rotation and spawn time of KT.<br>
<br>
The total effect of our mistake was to make 3 guilds wait one week each, so what seems reasonable to me is for us to wait 3 weeks for our next KT.<br>
<br>
NB - TL - LoM - FK - VoF - LoL - BotS - SotE<br>
becomes<br>
NB - TL - LoM - VoF - LoL - BotS - FK - SotE<br>
and we skip the turn we took out of place<br>
<br>
I know the other two GL's of FK feel that my proposal is still harsh and do not fully agree with me (since we did not intentionally ninja the spawn, why should we get punished like we did), but I personally feel that it is the right thing to do.<br>
