<br>
And yes, Noble Blade has always sent tells and discussed in RTA on nights with emergency patches when rotation mobs become FFA to avoid being eaten by the patch.  I still make sure we don't take mobs people plan on keeping their turns for by sending tells.<br>
<br>
It's odd you would treat rotations with more guilds on it as deserving of different penalties than those with smaller numbers, when I would argue that even more stringent care needs to be taken not to mess up and kill out of turn.  You have no one to blame but yourselves for KSing our mob, and how long it takes before you get to kill him again doesn't change my mind on how serious of a violation this is.  You killed out of turn, and the rules for that have been clear for a very long time.<br>
<br>
As for your analysis of what the effect is, I disagree.  You are minimalizing at best.  For one thing, you didn't directly interuppt LoM or TLs plans for the night.  Sure you residually affected TL and LoM by putting them off a week each as well, but you were a direct downer to how we ended our night.  Put yourself in our shoes - next night you plan on doing Vindi, Statue, King Tormax, and Yelinak - you get to Yelinak and find nothing but a mystery to solve as to where your mob is.  Then have it turn out that we KSed your mob.   I know if we KSed a mob of yours, you'd be plenty pissed at us, and understandably so.<br>
<br>
Your proposal is no penalty, and since we can't have our KT back, I don't see why you shouldn't accept the standing punishment for breaking rotations.  There is no reason you shouldn't have checked ahead of time, or come forward on your own about this situation. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xpedia>Xpedia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>EotF - Guild Rep</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/31/02 11:52:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=238.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re</span><hr size=1> I am a new rep for my guild, so i am paying more attn to these boards though I have often cruised them for the pure reading enjoyment of it all.  I have no dog in the fight.  I have a RL friend in FK, and friends in NB as well.  I have lots of good will for both guilds actually as you both are in my top 5 of respected guilds on the server.  I'm sure many have differing opinions but that is mine.<br>
