If I am not mistaken you will get to kill him again before SotE gets to go?  I can't believe no one else has laid into you for that one.  Did someone say something about math geniuses?  Either that or I am reading that wrong because its not entirely clear.  The other way I see to interpret it is that you all will skip that turn when it comes and take it the next time around, which is more or less what everyone else is saying (before SotE or before NB is one guild difference, big deal).  I may have missed the boat entirely on that one too, happens often.<br>
<br>
I don't think you should be held to a different standard than anyone else, but you shouldn't be able to pick your standard.  There seem to be two precedents to go on and one is much more palatable than the other.  No one wants to be punished, thats why its a punishment.  To say you are sorry and you feel bad is good, I commend you for that.  I don't think it is a good standard though to let people off with a &quot;sorry, we screwed up&quot; though.  The Rathe is orderly for a reason and to let things go can create a slippery slope<br>
<br>
I think that with a change or lapse in rules some screw ups are bound to happen, but I personally would take extra caution in breaking form the norm by sending tells to double check.  Bottom line is that there needs to be something put in place by the RTA that is agreed upon ahead of time for address this.  That way if it happens its a non issue and the motives behind it are irrelevant.  Its hard to hold someone to a standard that wasn't officially in place.<br>
<br>
My opinion, for what its worth.<br>
